The Progress-M27-M cargo craft was launched to the ISS earlier today, and, while exact details are unclear, it seems to be experiencing major issues in orbit and likely won't be able to rendezvous or dock. From what information we do have, the spacecraft is in an uncontrolled spin, uplink of commands and receipt of telemetry are erratic, and the antennae for the Kurs docking system hasn't deployed. On the last pass over the russian ground systems before this post, no telemetry was received at all.

